Prerequisites

Database table creation  
\===================

1. tt\_request\_status with below columns  
   1. Request\_id \- String \- This is the primary key. It holds the generated uuid  
   2. Status \- String \- In-queue, In-progress, Completed  
   3. Update\_ts \- Timestamp \- Last updated timestamp

   Sample value- 88-aaab-hhh-333, In-queue, 2024-11-01 00:01:00

   

2. Tt\_seller\_product\_sales  
   1. Seller\_id \- String  
   2. Date \- date  
   3. Product\_id \- String  
   4. Num\_items\_sold \- int  
   5. Revenue \- double  
   6. Commission \- double

Redis  
\=====

- Create a csv file with sellerid, productid, cost of it. Sample

S101,P100,200  
S101,P200,300

- Load the csv file into redis. Redis holds the cache data in key value pairs. So load the data as key \- seller id/product id and value \- cost  
- For example \- S101/P100, 200


Setup kafka broker  
\==============

Kafka topic creation  
\===============  
Create a kafka topic by name seller\_product\_data\_tp with 3 partitions. Since there are 3 partitions, 3 workers (consumers) can be created.

Client.py  
\======

1. submitTask(sellerId, jsonFile)  
   1. JSON file:   
      ￼  
      {  
      “req\_id” :   
      “Seller\_id” :   
      “Date” :   
      “Product\_sold” : \[ { “p1”, 10}, {“p2”, 2}, {“p3”, 1} \]  
      “Product\_return” : \[ {“p1”, 2} \]  
      }  
        
   2. This method has to invoke producer.py produce method to write the message into kafka topic.  
   3. Generate uuid and invoke repo.py\> writestatus method to write the requestid and status to the database  
   4. Return request id to the user.  
2. queryStatus(requestId)  
   1. This method has to invoke repo.py \> queryStatus method  
   2. Return the status   
3. queryResult(sellerId)  
   1. This method has to invoke repo.py \> queryResult method  
   2. Return list of SellerProductSales

   

Producer.py  
\======

1. produce(sellerId, jsonFile) \- Write the data to the  seller\_product\_data topic with sellerId as the key. This enables equal distribution

Repo.py  
\=======

1. writeStatus(requestId, status) \- insert the request id, status into tt\_request\_status table  
2. updateStatus(requestId, status) \- update the status for the given requestid  
3. queryStatus(requestId) \- query the tt\_requesst\_status table for the status using the requestId  
4. writeResults(sellerId, date, productId, itemsSold, revenue, commission)   
5. queryResults(sellerId) \- query tt\_seller\_product\_sales table for the given seller id.

Worker.py (Consumer)  
\=======

- Consume the message from kafka topic. After consuming a message do the following:  
  - Read json data from the message and convert into a SellerProductDetails object  
  - Create SalesDetails object with members \- items\_sold, revenue, items\_returned  
  - Create a dictionary with key as product and value as SalesDetails. Populate the dictionary using SellerProductDetails object. Read the  cost of the  product from redis for the given sellerId/ProductId.  
  - Invoke repo.py \> writeResults(sellerid, date, productId, itemssold, revene,comm)  
  - Invoke repo.py \> updateStatus(requestId)  
  - consumer.commit()
